   <mods:abstract>Jay does not feel equal to advising Floridablanca on the best manner for
            offering monetary assistance to the U.S. since he is a stranger to the resources of
            Spain In regard to building vessels, it has never been the policy of nations to expect
            the repayment of war loans until the war is over. If this is the only basis for making a
            loan to the U.S., such a plan will be fruitless. Jay is sure of the friendliness of
            Spain and that some plan will be worked out for paying the debts.</mods:abstract>
